Political Capital[b1: In the country the risk of the Hungarian Guard is increased
According to the Division for Risk Analysis (Risk Analysis Division) of the Capital Policy, the activity of the Hungarian Guard, formed in August this year with the support of the Movement for Better Hungary, has increased the political risk of Hungary and the region from a number of points of view.
In the company's "risk warning" it is written: in relation to the activity of the Hungarian Guard, the greatest political risk is the fact that "with the worsening ethnic tensions existing between the Roma and non-Jitan population of Hungary, even in the short term violent ethnic clashes can occur".
The main reason for this is that the Hungarian Guard's political strategy is probably the provocation of an event of this nature - the representative of the research institute added.
They affirmed that this is due to one of the main shortcomings of the protagonists of Hungarian political life: "the protagonists of public life handed over the public debate of the Roma problem to the representatives of radical and extremist political groups, who were able to base their political strategy on the discrepancies between Gypsys and Hungarians."
This aggravates the problem, prevents normal dialogue, strengthens extremists and increases the likelihood of the outbreak of violent conflicts - they estimate.
