Not even in the EU or North America are parties unitary.
Hungarian laws make a difference between national party, state party and holidays.
The holidays are mainly related to religious festivals and historical ephemerals.
Let us also celebrate the New Year: both the last day of the old year, and the first day of the new year is festive - the last one above all so that those who spent celebrating the old year can rest.
Throughout the year we have eleven parties written with red numbers on the calendar.
It is a national festival on 15 March in memory of the revolution of 1848 and 23 October, the commemorative day of the revolution of 1956.
On 20 August, we celebrate the foundation of the State, on 1 May, the feast of work, on 1 and 2 November, we remind our dead relatives and friends.
In addition, in our country they are two-day parties the Easter of Resurrection, Pentecost and Christmas.
According to the calendar, our state, national or religious parties rarely coincide with a weekend, so often one bridge is made when there is only one working day before or after the party.
In exchange for extended weekends like this, during the previous Saturdays you cannot be absent from work or school.
He is the minister of work who regulates in his specific decree when one has to work exactly in return for the day directly preceding or after the feast.
This legal standard is mandatory for all employers and their employees, as well as for employees and civil servants.
It is not mandatory, on the other hand, for companies and service institutions which, because of their function, work continuously even during holidays.
This year's work order can be changed only around the end of the year's parties: from December 24, life is practically stopped in the country, since according to the experiences, most people "punish" during the days between Christmas and the end of the year or take their holidays during these days.
